Elbit Imaging Rises to Month-High on Romania Hotel Refinance

-- B y   S u s a n   L e r n e r
-- 
2011-10-03T15:13:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-03/elbit-imaging-rises-most-in-week-after-romania-hotel-refinancing.html
Elbit Imaging Ltd. (EMIT)  rose to the
highest in almost a month after a unit of the investor in real
estate and medical companies completed a 71.5 million-euro ($96
million) refinancing of its Radisson Blu Hotel in Bucharest.  The shares climbed 5.7 percent to 9.126 shekels at the 4:30
p.m. close in  Tel Aviv , the highest level since Sept. 5. The
stock has declined 81 percent this year, giving the Tel Aviv-
based company a market value of 233 million shekels ($62
million).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Susan Lerner in Jerusalem at 
